Wow! I have never made PUDC before, or for that matter, even tasted it, but this was pretty stellar, despite the minor alterations I made. First, I don't own any cast iron- I just don't like it- so I melted the butter and brown sugar in a stainless steel pan, and transferred it to a 9" cake pan. Next time, I might try to keep the pan warm, as the caramel solidified very quickly, though most of it melted nicely while baking. Second, I too used gluten free flour. No problems there. Third, I had no juice, so I pureed the other half of the pineapple, and threw that in, pulp and all. Perfect! I added some lemon and almond extract in addition to the vanilla, and threw some dried cranberries into the batter. Finally, I had no rum, so I used Guaycura Licor de Damiana, but only in the batter, and not on top. It looked so pretty when it came out that I didn't want to add anything. A little of the sugar stuck to the pan, but came loose easily, and still looked pretty when sprinkled on top. Next time-- and there definitely WILL be a next time-- I'd like to add some nuts to the batter. Reducing the cardamom to two and half tsps kept the aroma very exotic, but the flavor was not overpowering. Everybody raved about this cake, and we had a very light dinner in anticipation of dessert, once the aroma overtook my kitchen. I found the cake to be very moist and flavorful. It seems, perfect as it was with all the changes I made as a first timer, like this would be a really hard one to mess up!

