Rating: 3
The topping is a little on the greasy side but recipes for the cast iron skillet usually are - released beautifully. Adjust butter in topping to your taste & type of pan accordingly. Can make the topping as for a Flan to cut the grease even more. The batter makes a classic european spice cake (e.g. Apple spice teacakes) & is supposed to have a soft crumb & will not hold chunks of fruit together like a dense carrot cake. So fruit has to be sliced thin and layered on the pan. This cake will also fall apart if too much rum or syrup is drizzled on top. A very nice teacake & when made in a cast iron skillet, has crunchy edges.

