Rating: 3
I received a fruit basket with a nice fresh pineapple in it so I made this cake yesterday with a couple of minor modifications. No cast iron skillet, so I put the butter-brown sugar mixture in a 9-inch square baking pan - all my round pans are springform and I wanted to avoid the leakage others (either here or as posted under other PUDC recipes) have experienced. Ground cardamom fresh from pods in mortar and pestle, about 1 1/2 teaspoons. The subtle hint of spice was just right. I used buttermilk instead of pineapple juice and added a little extra rum to the batter to thin it out a bit. The cake came out delicious; somewhat dense and didn't rise much (possibly from the buttermilk). I would add a litle soda if using buttermilk in the future (it's called for in the fresh PUDC recipe elsewhere on this site). A very homey yummy cake; certainly worth making!

