I used two small cake tins with thickly sliced pineapples - ring in the center and quartered slices around it - I juiced the leftover pineapple including the core, used less than 1 tsp of cardamom seeds and 1/4 c. less sugar in the batter. Next time I will also use less sugar in the topping and even less cardamom ground from seed. However, my boyfriend thought it was the best thing I've ever made and he doesn't have a sweet tooth and I'm not too bad cook but, not much of a baker.

Rating: 4
I will never make PUDC with anything but fresh pineapple from now on. This recipe was wonderful! I halved the amt of cardamom called for, since I used freshly ground pods and the balance was perfect. I also made this cake in a 12 inch skillet, which I think was the right size for the amount of butter and sugar called for in the topping. Also, don't be afraid to cut the pineapple rounds nice and thick - you'll be glad you did when you turn out the cake!

