Rating: 3
We made this cake in a 10x3" round professional cake pan to allow plenty of room on the sides to rise, and lined the bottom with parchment, spraying the paper and pan sides with non-stick baking spray. Since it was a larger pan, we increased the brown sugar mixture by one-half, which was perfect if you like a goo-ier tooped cake. We also used just 2 tsp of cardomom (ground from seeds) and it was unusual and perfectly spiced. We used fresh pineapple rings (made sure my husband dried them three times!) and added maraschino cherries to the middle of the rings and gaps. It turned out onto a platter perfectly when done and was so lovely, we e-mailed a picture to our parents right away. Was a big hit at our Easter dinner... next time will try it warm with vanilla ice cream - yum.

