This is a very good recipe; moist and flavorful. No beaten egg whites, as some recipes reccomend, but I like the resulting denseness. The second time I made this, I took a leaf from Cook's Illustrated's book: I used four tblsp butter and a cup of brown sugar to make the topping, and then cooked these together for four minutes to achieve a more caramelized consistency -- I liked the results very much -- a bit tarte-tatin-ish. Lacking a skillet, I did the cake in two stages and it came out beautifully. Also, in a pinch used canned pineapple which was, if less elegant, still very tasty.

