Rating: 4
I loved this recipe. It can be made much simpler than recipe lets on. I didn't bother with the sifting and the slow additions. I just whipped all the cake ingredients in order and made the cake in a non-stick cake pan. The brown sugar topping requires a lot more brown sugar to butter. Also, if you put the pineapple slices at a 45 deg angle to bottom of pan you really overlap them and the finished cake has a zig-zag crown-like trim at the top. Laying the pinapple flat doesn't fit enough pineapple in and then the cake is too dry. Put some foil under the cake pans because the brown sugar bottom tends to boil over the edges of the cake pan during baking. Loved it!

Rating: 4
